<subSubSection id="D1E76521FFDBFF97FF6BDDE2AC34F8F0" pageId="6" pageNumber="336" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="994236AAFFDBFF97FF6BDDE2AC34F8F0" blockId="6.[151,1436,1759,2036]" pageId="6" pageNumber="336">
<emphasis id="AB89EAB8FFDBFF97FF6BDDE2A919F96B" bold="true" box="[151,286,1759,1784]" pageId="6" pageNumber="336">Etymology.</emphasis>
The overall dorsal color of this insect resembles a solar eclipse by the moon. On the other hand this etymology refers to the French verb « éclipser » which means overshadowing, recalling that, for over a century, the general collection of 
<collectionCode id="FFECAE6FFFDBFF97FE75DC15A9D9F8AC" box="[393,478,1832,1855]" country="France" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34988" name="Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle" pageId="6" pageNumber="336">MNHN</collectionCode>
overshadowed this small species from the sight of specialists. 
<emphasis id="AB89EAB8FFDBFF97FB51DC1AAD2BF8AC" box="[1197,1324,1831,1855]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="336">Calagasma</emphasis>
means in Latin «beautiful jewel» which is not in contradiction with the beauty of 
<taxonomicName id="5EFD4D29FFDBFF97FC40DC71AC2BF8F7" box="[956,1068,1868,1892]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Calagasma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="336" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eclipsa">
<emphasis id="AB89EAB8FFDBFF97FC40DC71AC2BF8F7" box="[956,1068,1868,1892]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="336">C. eclipsa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
